==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anhele
<hw>An*hele"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>aneler</ets>, <ets>anheler</ets>. See <er>Anhelation</er>.]</ety>
<def>To pant; to be breathlessly anxious or eager
(<xex>for</xex>).</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>anhele</qex> . . . for the fruit of our convocation.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anhelose</ent>⟦br⟧
